          "type": "text",
          "text": "Done! I've created a 7-segment counter circuit with the following:\n\n**Hardware:**\n- 7-segment display (common cathode) on the right side\n- 7 series resistors (220Ω each) limiting current to each segment\n- Button on pin 9 (active-LOW with internal pull-up)\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Each button press increments the counter (0→1→2→...→9→0)\n- The 7-segment display updates immediately to show the current digit\n- De-bouncing logic prevents false counts from switch bounce\n\nThe sketch uses a simple lookup table with if/else chains for each digit (0–9), determining which segments light up for that number."
        }
